# IPL Data Analysis Project Phases :

## Phase 1: Understanding the Problem :
In this phase, I decided what I want to explore in IPL data.  
The main goal of this project is to understand player and team performance.
Some questions I want to answer:
- Which batsmen have scored the most runs?
- Which bowlers have taken the most wickets?
- Which teams perform better?
- Does winning the toss affect the match result?

## Phase 2: Data Collection :
In this phase, I collected the IPL dataset.

- The dataset is taken from Kaggle
- It includes two main files:
  - matches.csv (match-level data)
  - deliveries.csv (ball-by-ball data)


## Phase 3: Data Cleaning :
Before analysis, the data needs to be cleaned.
In this phase, I:
- Checked for missing values
- Removed unnecessary columns
- Fixed data types where needed
- Made the dataset easier to work with


## Phase 4: Data Exploration (EDA) :
This is the main part of the project.
In this phase, I explored the data to find useful insights.
I analyzed:
- Top batsmen (based on total runs)
- Top bowlers (based on wickets)
- Team performance
- Toss impact on match results


## Phase 5: Data Visualization :
In this phase, I used graphs to better understand the data.
I created:
- Bar charts for top players
- Charts for team performance
- Simple visual comparisons
Libraries used:
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn


## Phase 6: Insights and Conclusion :
In this phase, I summarized what I learned from the data.
Some key insights:
- Certain players consistently perform well
- Some teams perform better than others
- Toss can sometimes influence match results


## Phase 7: Future Improvements :
This project can be improved in the future by:
- Adding more recent IPL data
- Creating more advanced visualizations
- Building a prediction model
